Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
When I select 'Female' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select any Examination radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
Then I go to Page 03 and select 'Yes' in Contrast enhanced
Then I go to Page 06 of Pelvic MRI
And I click on 'Finding' radio button
And dropdown below 'Finding' is enabled

When I select 'Corpus uteri inflammation' from the dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Characterization I' tab is preselected
And 'I describe' button is preselected

When I select 'Characterization II' tab
Then slider 'T1w signal' is enabled
And slider 'T2w signal' is enabled

And 'Strong' radio button is enabled
And 'Low' radio button is enabled
And 'No' radio button is enabled

And 'Thickened uterosacral ligaments' checkbox is enabled
And 'Marked (peri-)uterine vessels' checkbox is enabled

And 'Ovarian vein thrombosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Peritoneal contrast enhancement' checkbox is enabled
And 'Ileus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hydroureter' checkbox is enabled

And 'Ascites' checkbox is enabled

And 'Differential diagnosis' dropdown is enabled

When I drag 'T1w signal' to 'Hyperintense' position
Then the slider stays at the 'Hyperintense' position

When I drag 'T2w signal' to 'Hyperintense' position
Then the slider stays at the 'Hyperintense' position

When I select 'Strong' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Low' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Thickened uterosacral ligaments' checkbox
Then 'Contrast enhancement' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Ovarian vein thrombosis' checkbox
Then 'Right' checkbox is enabled
And 'Left' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Peritoneal contrast enhancement' checkbox
Then 'Strong' radio button is enabled
And 'Low' radio button is enabled
And 'No' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Ascites' checkbox
Then 'T1w signal increase' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hemosiderin' checkbox is enabled
And 'Focal' checkbox is enabled
And 'Generalized' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Endometritis' from the dropdown
Then 'PID' checkbox is enabled
